INSERT INTO `question` (`id`, `quiz_id`, `title`, `type`, `number_of_options`, `options`, `correct_answers`, `order`) VALUES ('1', '6', '&lt;p&gt;A 20-year-old female presents with a 5 day history of vaginal discharge. Sexually active but not using contraception. Has had same partner for past year. Pelvic examination shows normal external genitalia. There is a moderate amount of malodorous, thin, gray discharge coating the vaginal walls. The vulva and cervix appear normal. There is no cervical motion tenderness on bimanual examination. The pH of the vaginal fluid is 5.0. Swabs show that patient has a bacterial infection. Symptoms consistent with bacterial vaginosis. A urine pregnancy test is negative. Which of the following is the most appropriate pharmacologic treatment?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Metronidazole\",\"Ceftriaxone\",\"Miconazole\",\"Azithromycin\",\"Doxycycline\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('2', '6', '&lt;p&gt;A 23-year-old woman comes to the clinic because of a change in vaginal discharge. Over the past week she has noticed a foul smelling discharge, particularly after intercourse. She denies any pain, itching or irregular bleeding. She has an intrauterine contraceptive device that was inserted 2 years ago. Vital signs are normal. Physical examination shows a foul-smelling, thin, whitish-gray vaginal discharge. There is no adnexal or cervical motion tenderness on bimanual examination.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Gonococcal urethritis\",\"Trichomonas vaginitis\",\"Bacterial vaginosis\",\"Candidiasis\",\"Physiologic leukorrhea\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('3', '6', '&lt;p&gt;A 25-year-old woman comes to the office for an examination. She is a student and exercises regularly. She is sexually active with a partner and uses oral contraceptive pills. Medical history is noncontributory. Family history includes a grandmother with coronary artery disease. Her temperature is 36.8°C (98°F), pulse is 87/min, respirations are 18/min, and blood pressure is 152/91 mm Hg. Physical examination shows no abnormalities. Over the next 3 months, her blood pressure is repeatedly elevated at clinic visits. Which of the following is the most appropriate first step in management?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Alprazolam\",\"Cessation of oral contraceptive pills\",\"Hydrochlorothiazide\",\"Lisinopril\",\"Watchful waiting\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('4', '6', '&lt;p&gt;A 21 yr old female presents to the surgery complaining of pain during intercourse. She gives a history of unprotected sex with multiple partners. No recent pregnancy. Physical exam nad, except for moderate cervical motion tenderness while performing pelvic exam. What condition could she possibly have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Candidiasis\",\"Chlamydia\",\"Gonorrheoa\",\"Bacterial Vaginosis\",\"IBS\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('5', '6', '&lt;p&gt;15yr old female presents with a history of irregular menstrual periods that range from 2 weeks to 3months apart. She reports heavy menstrual flow which lasts up to seven days. She is not sexually active. Her temperature is 37.1°C (98.7°F), pulse is 85/min, respirations are 16/min, and blood pressure is 121/83 mm Hg. BMI is 29kg/m2. She has coarse hairs on her chin, arms, and abdomen. Weight gain around abdomen and she is not pregnant. Which of the following is the most appropriate treatment for the patient’s condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Hysterectomy\",\"Clomiphene\",\"Metformin\",\"Oral contraceptive pill\",\"Surgery\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('6', '17', '&lt;p&gt;A 10-year old girl is brought to her pediatrician’s office by her parents because of a new onset of skin lesions for the past 3 days. Her father says that the patient had an initial lesion of a small pustule which quickly progressed into an extensive rash. Physical examination shows the following: Which of the following is the most likely causative organism?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Human herpes virus 6\",\"Varicella-zoster virus\",\"Staphylococcus aureus\",\"Streptococcus agalactia\",\"Propionibacterium acnes\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('7', '17', '&lt;p&gt;A 19-year-old man comes to the clinic because of a rash that started as a single lesion a few days ago. It has since spread throughout his chest and back. The patient had an upper respiratory infection nine days ago. Physical examination shows salmon pink patches, as seen below. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Pityriasis Rosea\",\"Syphillis\",\"Porphyria\",\"Tinea Corporis\",\"Eczema\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('8', '17', '&lt;p&gt;A 36-year-old man who recently emigrated from Chile comes to the physician for a wellness checkup. He states that he had worked as a farmer for many years. His jobs included spraying plants with pesticide, harvesting crops, and plowing the fields. The pesticide he worked with contains arsenic. Which of the following skin conditions is he most at risk for developing?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Acral lentiginous melanoma\",\"Dishydrotic eczema\",\"Basal cell carcinoma\",\"Scleroderma\",\"Squamous cell carcinoma\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('9', '17', '&lt;p&gt;A 73-year-old male comes to the office with a itchy skin rash. The lesions are round, oval, and erythematous on both legs. There is noticeable xerosis of the affected skin. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Tinea corporis\",\"Seborrheic keratosis\",\"Bullous phemigoid\",\"Tinea versicolor\",\"Nummular eczema\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('10', '17', '&lt;p&gt;A 22-year-old woman comes to the clinic because of blisters on her hands. She recently got a summer job designing costumes for a local theatre production group. She says that the lesions first appeared on the lateral edges of her fingers and then spread to her palms. The lesions are very itchy and somewhat tender. Physical examination shows tense vesicles on her fingers and the palms of her hands without any associated erythema. Which of the following is true about this condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"The lesions are associated with sweat gland dysfunction\",\"Triggered by exposure to nickel\",\"Associated with coeliac disease\",\"It is psoriasis\",\"It is associated with systemic lupus erythematous in 50% of patients\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('11', '21', '&lt;p&gt;A 65-year-old woman comes to the office because of problems with her hearing and ‘ear fullness.’ She reports that she has noticed a low pitch noise that others don’t hear that sounds like being by rthe ocean, and a decrease in hearing in her left ear. She has also been having intermittent episodes of dizziness when she feels like the room is spinning. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis for this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Labyrinthitis\",\"Meniere\\u2019s Disease\",\"BPPV\",\"Migraine with aura\",\"Multiple Sclerosis\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('12', '21', '&lt;p&gt;A 25yr old male comes to the out of hours clinic with an inability to open his mouth. He has pain and swelling in his neck which has worsened over the past day. He has bilateral swelling of the floor of the mouth involving his submandibular and sublingual glands. His molars on the right side are decayed and there is an abscess around the back molars. The skin of his upper neck is red but intact. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Periodontitis\",\"Sialolithiasis\",\"Kawasaki Disease\",\"Ludwig\\u2019s Angina\",\"Stevens Johnson Syndrome\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('13', '21', '&lt;p&gt;A 53-year-old woman comes to the office because she thinks her hearing has worsened in her left ear. She has not noticed any discharge or felt any dizziness. Her temperature is 37.3 °C P: 72 RR:12 and BP : 132/78. She has conductive hearing loss in left ear. Physical examination shows no erythema or tenderness of the pinna or auricle. The ear examination shows a retracted tympanic membrane and squamous debris. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Mastoiditis\",\"Impacted wax\",\"Chronic Otitis Media\",\"Cholesteatoma\",\"Malignant Otitis Externa\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('14', '21', '&lt;p&gt;22 Year old female presents with a history of vertigo, nausea and tinnitus for 2 days. Recent upper respiratory tract infection that was treated with anti virals. She has mild hearing loss and a positive Dix-Hallpike manoeuver. Based on the patient’s history and symptoms, which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"BPPV\",\"Labyrinthitis\",\"Vestibular Neuritis\",\"Meniere\\u2019s disease\",\"Tension type headache\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('15', '21', '&lt;p&gt;A previously healthy 5-year-old boy comes to the office because of fever for the past two days. His mother reports onset of vomiting and dysphagia earlier this morning but denies any diarrhea, rhinorrhea or upper respiratory symptoms. She notes that he just started kindergarten, and there have been a few other children out sick. His temperature is 38.8°C (101.9°F). His posterior oropharynx is erythematous with an inflamed uvula and enlarged symmetric masses. He also has enlarged, tender anterior cervical lymphadenopathy. He is quite resistant, constantly moving his head to avoid the examination. Which of the following is the most appropriate treatment?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Immediate surgical drainage by ENT\",\"Oral penicillin\",\"Rest and paracetamol\",\"Tonsillectomy\",\"IV antibiotics\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('16', '26', '&lt;p&gt;25-year-old man comes to the surgery because of severe leg cramps. He says that he has \\”dark urine\\” and that earlier in the morning he had trouble lifting a glass object object. Physical examination shows tenderness in his hamstrings and quadriceps when palpated. Urine dipstick is positive for blood. Which of the following is most likely a potential complication of this patient’s condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Acute Myocardial Infarction\",\"Acute kidney injury\",\"Haemothorax\",\"Acute respiratory distress syndrome\",\"Tension pneumothorax\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('17', '26', '&lt;p&gt;A 48-year-old woman comes to the emergency department because of ‘burning, bloody urine’. She has been urinating more frequently for the past 2 days, but she denies polydipsia, vaginal discharge, back pain, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, or fevers. Physical examination shows that she is afebrile and her other vital signs are stable. Her abdomen is soft, non-tender and there is no flank tenderness. Urine dipstick is positive for leukocyte esterase and nitrites. Which of the following is the most appropriate initial treatment option?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Doxycycline\",\"amoxycillin\",\"Nitrofurantoin\",\"Trimethoprim\",\"Cephalexin\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('18', '26', '&lt;p&gt;A 27-year-old man comes to the surgery because of severe flank pain for an hour. The pain woke him from his sleep, He rates the pain as a 10 on a 10-point scale. Temperature is 36.7°. He appears to be constantly moving and unable to get comfortable. No medical problems. Had kidney stones about a year ago but since then he has been well. What is the likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"AAA Abdominal aortic aneurysm\",\"Appendicitis\",\"Ruptured bladder\",\"Small bowel obstruction\",\"Hydronephrosis\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('19', '26', '&lt;p&gt;A 50-year-old woman comes to the surgery because of severe, colicky left-sided abdominal pain. Urinalysis shows trace of blood. Her T: 37.2° , P:70. RR18 and BP: 160/90 mm Hg. Her BMI is 23. Her medical history is significant for celiac disease that was diagnosed 20 years ago. She avoids gluten and takes vitamins to “stay healthy”. Which of the following is most likely present in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Osteomalacia\",\"Vitamin D excess\",\"Vitamin D deficiency\",\"Vitamin C deficiency\",\"Hypophosphatemia\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('20', '26', '&lt;p&gt;A 25-year-old previously healthy woman comes to the surgery because of 2 days of mild nausea and vomiting. She denies recent sick contacts or eating anything out of the ordinary. She has maintained good oral intake of food and fluids over the past two days, but has noticed increasing malaise and a dull pain on her right side. She complains of mild dysuria and urinary frequency for the past 2 days. Medical history is negative for kidney stones T:38.3P:100 RR:18 BP: 11/70 Physical examination shows no definite CVA tenderness. Urine dipstick positive for leucocytes. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis? Select all that apply&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Acute cystitis\",\"UTI\",\"Kidney stones\",\"Appendicitis\",\"Pyelonephritis\"]', '[\"1\",\"2\"]', '0'), ('21', '31', '&lt;p&gt;A 22-year-old woman comes to the office because of frequent urination for 2 days. She states that she also feels a fullness and pressure in her bladder. She gets this frequently and the urine tests are usually negative. She is sexually active with a new partner and uses condoms. Does have a history of dyspareunia before this partner, but recent swabs at STD clinic were negative. She has a history of endometriosis and irritable bowel syndrome. No known allergies. Family history includes type 2 diabetes in both parents. T: 36.5 P:72 RR16 BP: 122/76 .No suprapubic tenderness to palpation. Urine dipstick is negative. Which of the following is the most likely cause of her symptoms?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Cystitis\",\"Diabetes mellitus\",\"Endometriosis\",\"Vaginitis\",\"Chlamydia urethritis\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('22', '31', '&lt;p&gt;A 60-year-old woman, gravida 6, para 6, comes to the office because of a bulge in her vagina and pain with intercourse for the past 10 years. She has been experiencing urinary incontinence as well. Her medical history includes six vaginal deliveries without complications. Her last menstrual period was 11 years ago. Pelvic examination shows a bulging anterior vaginal wall with normal cervical positioning. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Vaginal prolapse\",\"Cystocele\",\"Enterocele\",\"Rectocele\",\"Uterine prolapse\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('23', '31', '&lt;p&gt;A 65-year-old post menopausal female presents to the office because of terrible vulvar itching, which has been ongoing for the past several months. The patient has been applying over-the-counter anti-fungal agents without relief. Physical examination reveals white plaques on her labia minora and majora. A punch biopsy of the lesions is performed and atypia is not present. Which of the following is the most effective treatment for this condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Estrogen cream\",\"Chemotherapy\",\"Excision\",\"Fluconazole\",\"Topical corticosteroids\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('24', '31', '&lt;p&gt;A 60-year-old woman comes to the office because of vaginal bleeding for the past 2 days. Her last menstrual period was 7 years ago and she has not had any bleeding until now. Pelvic examinationshows no abnormalities. An endometrial biopsy is performed and reveals grade I endometrial adenocarcinoma, and staging is done via a CT scan. Which of the following is the most appropriate initial step in management?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Chemotherapy\",\"Colposcopy with biopsy\",\"Dilation and curettage\",\"Hysterectomy\",\"Radiation therapy\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('25', '31', '&lt;p&gt;A 22-year old woman comes into the primary care office with a 1 week history of foul-smelling vaginal discharge. She reports being sexually active with multiple partners and inconsistent condom use. On pelvic exam, her vaginal mucosa is erythematous and friable, and her cervix shows erythema with pinpoint areas of exudation. A wet mount preparation of the discharge shows numerous multi-flagellated organisms. Which of the following is the next best step in management?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Treat with fluconazole\",\"Treat with metronidazole\",\"Treat with ceftriaxone\",\"Treat with nitrofurantoin\",\"Reassurance\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('26', '33', '&lt;p&gt;To what drug does paroxysmal hemicrania respond well?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Amitriptyline\",\"Topiramate\",\"Verapamil\",\"Indomethacin\",\"Gabapentin\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('27', '33', '&lt;p&gt;35-year-old female presents to the surgery complaining of right-sided facial pain. She is complaining of/o stabbing electric shocks exacerbated by eating, brushing her teeth and a brisk breeze across her face. The pain lasts a few seconds and rarely up to a couple of minutes. Physical examination shows normal facial sensation, normal bulk in the masseters bilaterally, and intact extra-ocular muscles. Which is the most appropriate treatment in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Calcium Gluconate\",\"Carbamazepine\",\"Valproic acid\",\"Clonazepam\",\"Prednisone\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('28', '33', '&lt;p&gt;48yr old females comes to the surgery at 14h00 complaining of headache since 3am that day. She is complaining that the pain is unilateral and throbbing in nature. The patient says she was watching her sons school rehearsal not long before the onset of the headache. She says the rehearsal used strobe lighting for visual effects. She also mentions hallucinating light beams ‘dancing in front of her’ after the show. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Migraine\",\"SAH\",\"Cluster Headache\",\"Epilepsy\",\"Tension headache\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('29', '33', '&lt;p&gt;28yr old female presents with a severe headache that started 4hrs ago. Describes the headache as pulsating and localised to right eye. No relief with paracetamol and ibuprofen. Which of the following drugs would you consider helping with her acute symptoms?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Metoclopramide\",\"Naproxen\",\"Ondansetron\",\"Verapamil\",\"Sumatriptan\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('30', '33', '&lt;p&gt;40-year-old male attends the out of hours centre complaining of a severe headache that woke him from his sleep about 4 hrs ago. Complaining of a stabbing and burning pain located behind his right eye. He also has nasal congestion on that side He had something similar around the same month 5yrs ago. He gets these every year at the same time. PMH nil except he smokes for past 30 years about one pack a day. Physical examination reveals normal intraocular pressures bilaterally, normal visual acuity, and no fluorescein dye uptake on either cornea. His right eyelid is drooping with slight pupil constriction. Which of the following is the most appropriate preventative measure for this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Verapamil\",\"Propranolol\",\"Sumatriptan\",\"Ibuprofen\",\"Paracetamol\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('31', '36', '&lt;p&gt;A 58-year-old man with a BMI of 32 comes to the surgery. He states he gets very short of breath after climbing a flight of stairs. His SOB is associated with a cough and productive green sputum. He has had symptoms like these for at least four months out of the year over the past decade, but they have been consistently present for the past 6 months and seem to be worsening in severity. The patient admits to smoking about a pack of cigarettes a week for the past 20 years. He has never received flu vaccine. He is worried that this could be related to his family history of cardiac issues. He is afebrile, there is no sign of oedema and heart sounds appear to be normal. Which of the following findings is most likely to be observed on physical examination?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"COPD\",\"Asthma\",\"Obstructive Sleep Apnoea\",\"Heart Failure\",\"Emphysema\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('32', '36', '&lt;p&gt;A 30-year-old man comes to the clinic because of fatigue and sleepiness throughout the day. His past medical, family, and social histories are non-contributory. His wife says he snores very loudly while sleeping and she has recently noticed that he will stop breathing.momentarily, multiple times throughout the night. spo2: 90%. He has a BMI of 33kg/m2, having gained 5.4-kg (12-lb) over the past year without any significant lifestyle or dietary changes. You advise the patient to lose weight and see a relevant specialist. Which is the most likely cause of this patient’s condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Anaemia\",\"Obstructive Sleep Apnoea\",\"Orthopnea\",\"Diabetes Mellitus\",\"Heart Failure\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('33', '36', '&lt;p&gt;A 23-year-old college student comes to the surgery with a 2 day history of a non-productive cough, feeling feverish and “feeling sick” for 2 days. She says she has a final exam tomorrow and wants some medicine so she feels better during the test. Her temperature is 37.2°C, P87/min, RR18/min, and BP 117/78 mm Hg. Examination shows clear lung sounds bilaterally in all fields. There is no cervical lymphadenopathy. She has some pharyngeal erythema with neither exudates nor vesicles. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in the management of this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Refer to emergency department for intravenous antibiotics\",\"Refer for chest x-ray\",\"Discharge with oral antibiotics\",\"Reassure and discharge\",\"Give oral steroids\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('34', '36', '&lt;p&gt;A 5-year-old girl is brought to the emergency department by her parents because of a sore throat and difficulty swallowing that began 3 days ago. Her temperature is 39.2 °C , pulse is 92/minute, respiration rate 22/minute, and blood pressure is 100/73 mm Hg. Her O2 saturation of 98% on room air. Physical examination shows an erythematous oropharynx, bilateral tonisillar exudates, and cervical lymphadenopathy. During the examination, the patient resists moving her head and begins drooling. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Meningitis\",\"Croup\",\"Epiglottitis\",\"Peritonsillar abscess\",\"Retropharyngeal abscess\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('35', '36', '&lt;p&gt;46-year-old man comes to the surgery with 3 day history of shortness of breath and increasing difficulty in breathing. He has a productive cough with green and yellow phlegm, with dyspnea that worsens with minimal exertion. He has experienced no fever, chills or chest pain. He is otherwise generally well except from a morning cough that brings up white sputum which he has been for many years. He has a 40 pack year history of smoking. No immunization history. SPO2 88% on room air and no cyanosis. Prolonged expiratory phase and bilateral expiry wheeze on auscultation. What is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'single_choice', '5', '[\"Acute exacerbation of COPD\",\"Bronchial pneumonia\",\"Bronchiectasis\",\"Congestive cardiac failure\",\"Viral pneumonia\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('36', '85', '&lt;p&gt;The 4 main types of eating disorders are:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Anorexia, Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders and Binge Eating\",\"Gluttony, Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders and Binge Eating\",\"Anorexia, Bad breath, forced vomiting and Binge Eating\",\"Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders, intermittent fasting and Binge Eating\"]', '[\"1\"]', '1'), ('37', '86', '&lt;p&gt;56yr old male with a history of chronic fatigue attends the surgery. He states he has difficulty sleeping and finds it hard to concentrate. you notice he has called 111 a few times and come to the surgery with similar symptoms 3 times in the past month. Which condition does he likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Schizophrenia\",\"Obsessive Compulsive Disorder\",\"Generalised anxiety Disorder\",\"Psychosis\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('38', '86', '&lt;p&gt;A 85-year-old male attends a surgery appointment accompanied by his wife. She complains that his memory has been gradually getting worse and that he has difficulty buttoning his shirt. On interviewing him, you find that he has trouble finding words. Which condition does he likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Parkinsons\",\"Alzheimers\",\"Delirium\",\"Schizophrenia\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('39', '86', '&lt;p&gt;18yr old patient presents with her mother who is concerned as daughter regularly abuses alcohol and has multiple sexual partners. Physical examination shows numerous cuts on her forearm. Which of the following is most likely present in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Borderline personality disorders\",\"Histrionic personality disorder\",\"Narcissistic personality disorder\",\"Obsessive compulsive personality disorder\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('40', '87', '&lt;p&gt;Trauma can have the following impact on staff.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Secondary traumatic stress when presence of PTSD symptoms caused by indirect exposure to other people\\u2019s traumatic experiences.\",\"Vicarious trauma where the cumulative effect of working with traumatized youth and their families that leads to negative changes in how staff view themselves, others, and the world.\",\"Answers 1 and 2.\",\"None of the above.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('41', '87', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following apply when a child has suffered trauma?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Listen to children \\u2013 both verbal and nonverbal.\",\"Always consider if any safeguarding issues are present.\",\"Recognize your limitations and consult colleagues and referral agencies.\",\"All of the above.\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('42', '87', '&lt;p&gt;What is trauma?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"It means acquired brain injury as a result of unregulated stress\",\"It is an accident and injury that has no effect on the brain\",\"It is a mental health illness similar to depression\",\"None of the above\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('43', '88', '&lt;p&gt;If we take on too many tasks without prioritising:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"We will be seen as hard working and more likely to get promoted\",\"We will be liked by everyone even if we get exhausted\",\"We can end up not meeting targets and this could reflect poorly on our overall performance at work.\",\"We are more likely to be friends with management and get invited to dinner parties.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('44', '88', '&lt;p&gt;Healthy Personal Boundaries are,&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Taking responsibility for your own actions and emotions, while NOT taking responsibility for the actions or emotions of others.\",\"Taking responsibility for everyone problems and ensuring they are solved.\",\"Being rigid and uncompromising.\",\"Being inflexible and ensuring that no one enters your space.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('45', '88', '&lt;p&gt;What are boundaries?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Boundaries are basic guidelines that people create to establish how others can behave around them.\",\"Boundaries means that no one can sit in your chair in the tearoom.\",\"It is the setting of standards of how to practice safely in hospitals.\",\"None of the above.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '3'), ('46', '89', '&lt;p&gt;Any decision to deprive an individual of their liberty can be challenged.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"1\"]', '1'), ('47', '89', '&lt;p&gt;The person who chairs a best interest meeting will always be the decision maker.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('48', '89', '&lt;p&gt;All care providers need to be aware and comply with the requirements of the Mental Capacity Act.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"1\"]', '3'), ('49', '91', '&lt;p&gt;What is self harm&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Self harm is a behaviour and not a mental illness\",\"It is an attempt to get gifts\",\"Self harm is a mental illness\",\"Self harm is taking part in dangerous sport.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '1'), ('50', '91', '&lt;p&gt;RCADS stands for:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Record conversations about drug socialization\",\"Revised anxiety and depression scale\",\"Repetitive conversations aid disease screening\",\"Review anxiety and dependency scale\"]', '[\"2\"]', '2'), ('51', '91', '&lt;p&gt;When dealing with children who self harm, staff may feel&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Shock and horror\",\"Feelings of distress and helplessness\",\"Anger and Frustration\",\"All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '3'), ('52', '93', '&lt;p&gt;If we take on too many tasks without prioritising:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"We will be seen as hard working and more likely to get promoted\",\"We will be liked by everyone even if we get exhausted\",\"We can end up not meeting targets and this could reflect poorly on our overall performance at work.\",\"We are more likely to be friends with management and get invited to dinner parties.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('53', '93', '&lt;p&gt;Healthy Personal Boundaries are,&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Taking responsibility for your own actions and emotions, while NOT taking responsibility for the actions or emotions of others.\",\"Taking responsibility for everyone problems and ensuring they are solved.\",\"Being rigid and uncompromising.\",\"Being inflexible and ensuring that no one enters your space.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('54', '93', '&lt;p&gt;What are boundaries?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Boundaries are basic guidelines that people create to establish how others can behave around them.\",\"Boundaries means that no one can sit in your chair in the tearoom.\",\"It is the setting of standards of how to practice safely in hospitals.\",\"None of the above.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '3'), ('55', '95', '&lt;p&gt;Any decision to deprive an individual of their liberty can be challenged.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('56', '95', '&lt;p&gt;The person who chairs a best interest meeting will always be the decision maker.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('57', '95', '&lt;p&gt;All care providers need to be aware and comply with the requirements of the Mental Capacity Act.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"True\",\"False\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('58', '97', '&lt;p&gt;The 4 main types of eating disorders are:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Anorexia, Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders and Binge Eating\",\"Gluttony, Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders and Binge Eating\",\"Anorexia, Bad breath, forced vomiting and Binge Eating\",\"Bulimia, Atypical eating disorders, intermittent fasting and Binge Eating\"]', '[\"1\"]', '1'), ('59', '97', '&lt;p&gt;When working with people with an eating disorder and their family members or carers (as appropriate):&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"As long as you maintain privacy and confidentiality, dignity is not an important consideration\",\"You can hold discussions in public places and include strangers in discussions about the persons eating disorder\",\"You should hold discussions in places where confidentiality, privacy and dignity can be respected\",\"It is not important to maintain confidentiality and you can agree to keep secrets\"]', '[\"3\"]', '2'), ('60', '97', '&lt;p&gt;When communicating with people with an eating disorder and their family members or carers&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Be sensitive when discussing a person\\u2019s weight and appearance\",\"Be aware that family members or carers may feel guilty and responsible for the eating disorder\",\"Show empathy, compassion and respect\",\"All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '3'), ('61', '100', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is a benefit of the early diagnosis of a mental health condition, dementia or a learning disability important?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"It allows people to develop stigma and stereotypes\",\"It enables the social model of disability to be put in place\",\"It enables the individual and their family to plan for their future care and support needs\",\"It allows the individual to get a second opinion\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('62', '100', '&lt;p&gt;What should you do if you are concerned that an individual’s needs have changed and need to be reassessed?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Raise your concerns following reporting procedures and agreed ways of working\",\"Do nothing, the matter is confidential\",\"Discuss your concerns with your family or friends\",\"Contact the Care Quality Commission to report your concerns immediately\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('63', '100', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the answers below describes the emotions experienced by someone living with major depression?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Hallucinations and delusions\",\"Feelings of sadness that don\\u2019t last long\",\"Feelings of hopelessness that do not go away\",\"Extreme happiness followed by sadness\"]', '[\"3\"]', '3'), ('64', '101', '&lt;p&gt;Which is the minimum observation period&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"A mental health patient should be observed every 120minutes\",\"Mental health patients need observing every 15-30minutes\",\"Mental health patients need to be observed every 60minutes\",\"Mental health patients do not need any observations\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('65', '101', '&lt;p&gt;How many guiding principles are there?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"7\",\"6\",\"5\",\"4\"]', '[\"3\"]', '2'), ('66', '101', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is true for high risk patients?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Is the patient at risk of harming themselves?\",\"Is the patient at risk of harming other people?\",\"Does the patient require an increased level of nursing\\/personal care?\",\"All of the above\",\"Is the patient likely to abscond from the unit?\"]', '[\"4\"]', '3'), ('67', '106', '&lt;p&gt;A 25 year old female presents with breast pain and says she is concerned as she has a family history of breast cancer with both her mother dying of the disease at 30 and her sister being diagnosed with the disease at 31. What is the implication of this for this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"There is no significance of such a history\",\"There is a significantly increased risk of this person developing breast cancer\",\"The patient is at significantly increased risk of developing all types of cancer\",\"There is no benefit in enrolling such a patient into a screening programme\",\"There is no benefit in offering genetic counselling & screening\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('68', '106', '&lt;p&gt;In terms of history taking which one of the following best describes the role of the social history?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"To identify risk factors for specific disease processes which may need further investigation \\/ management? It also provides an opportunity to offer health promotion advice\",\"To identify if the person takes part in any illegal activities\",\"To enable an assessment to be made as to the character of person that you are dealing with\",\"To assess a persons overall fitness level\",\"To provide an assessment of a person\\u2019s mental state\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('69', '106', '&lt;p&gt;A 38 year old female attends for her cervical screen. Your proceed to complete her records as you notice there is some missing data. Which one of the following needs to be specifically asked about when enquiring about a person’s social history?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Health of parents and siblings\",\"Medication allergies and intolerances\",\"Any factors which may indicate low mood\",\"Alcohol intake and smoking\",\"Any recent hospitalisations\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('70', '106', '&lt;p&gt;You are mentoring a student practitioner in your clinical environment. You are demonstrating the importance of taking a structured history using a medical model. When undertaking a systems enquiry which one of the following describes the activity that you will undertake?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Ask questions about any recent travel, smoking or exercise\",\"Ask if they have been in close contact with anyone else who is ill.\",\"Ask the person if there is anything else that they would like to add to the story\",\"Ask questions about each body system and related symptoms\",\"Reflect the persons history back to them to confirm what they told you.\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('71', '106', '&lt;p&gt;A 52 yr old male attends for his routine blood check. He has a blood pressure of 150/88. He also states he is a smoker. In discussions surrounding smoking which one of the following best describes “pack years”?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"The total number of years that an individual has been smoked for.\",\"One pack year equates to the smoking of twenty cigarettes a day for one year\",\"The number of packs that a person smokes per day\",\"A calculation used to quantify exposure to tobacco smoke in a standardised manner\",\"The number of years that a person has smoked for before developing symptoms of a smoking related disorder\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('72', '138', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is a benefit of the early diagnosis of a mental health condition, dementia or a learning disability important?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"It allows people to develop stigma and stereotypes\",\"It enables the social model of disability to be put in place\",\"It enables the individual and their family to plan for their future care and support needs\",\"It allows the individual to get a second opinion\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('73', '138', '&lt;p&gt;What should you do if you are concerned that an individual’s needs have changed and need to be reassessed?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Raise your concerns following reporting procedures and agreed ways of working\",\"Do nothing, the matter is confidential\",\"Discuss your concerns with your family or friends\",\"Contact the Care Quality Commission to report your concerns immediately\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('74', '138', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the answers below describes the emotions experienced by someone living with major depression?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Hallucinations and delusions\",\"Feelings of sadness that don\\u2019t last long\",\"Feelings of hopelessness that do not go away\",\"Extreme happiness followed by sadness\"]', '[\"3\"]', '3'), ('75', '141', '&lt;p&gt;What is unique about multiple sclerosis&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Your immune system normally protects you from foreign invaders like viruses and bacteria.\",\"Attacks cause hard scars (sclerosis) that interfere with nerve signals.\",\"The immune system launches attacks against the protective covering of nerve fibers in your brain and spinal cord.\",\"The symptoms are visible at the early stage.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('76', '141', '&lt;p&gt;The client newly diagnosed with multiple sclerosis (MS) states, “I don’t understand how I got multiple sclerosis. Is it genetic?” On which statement should the nurse base the response?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"There is no evidence suggesting there is any chromosomal involvement in developing MS.\",\"Multiple sclerosis is caused by a recessive gene, so both parents had to have the gene for the client to get MS.\",\"Genetics may play a role in susceptibility to MS, but the disease may be caused by a virus.\",\"Multiple sclerosis is caused by an autosomal dominant gene on the Y chromosome, so only fathers can pass it on.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '2'), ('77', '141', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following statements is true?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"MS is less common in tropical countries near the equator that get lots of sunshine.\",\"Ms is caused mainly by genes.\",\"Ms is caused by lacks certain vitamins.\",\"Ms generates from obesity.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '3'), ('78', '140', '&lt;p&gt;What causes autism?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Not being cautious and responsible during pregnancy.\",\"Autism is caused by low birth weight.\",\"Autism develops when on is born to family with mental health problems.\",\"Autism develops from a combination of genetic and nongenetic, or environmental, influences.\"]', '[\"4\"]', '1'), ('79', '140', '&lt;p&gt;What are some of the strength and abilities of people with autism?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Being precise, honest and detail orientated\",\"Learning to hide signs of autism to \\u2018fit in\\u2019.\",\"Very good listeners.\",\"They are socially active.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '2'), ('80', '140', '&lt;p&gt;Which one of the following is regarded as positive support strategy that can be given to autistic people?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Speech therapy so that they can learn how to improve on how they understand speech and language.\",\"Encourage them to socialise as to maintain relationships.\",\"Individualised support is key since every case is different from one person to the next.\",\"Family training after diagnosis.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '3'), ('81', '139', '&