u are demonstrating the importance of taking a structured history using a medical model. When undertaking a systems enquiry which one of the following describes the activity that you will undertake?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Ask questions about any recent travel, smoking or exercise\",\"Ask if they have been in close contact with anyone else who is ill.\",\"Ask the person if there is anything else that they would like to add to the story\",\"Ask questions about each body system and related symptoms\",\"Reflect the persons history back to them to confirm what they told you.\"]', '[\"4\"]', '4'), ('148', '287', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following statements is true?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"It is important to only ask yes\\/no questions about mental health so that you have clear answers.\",\"You should ask both the child and parent about mental health concerns.\",\"Asking about suicide increases risk.\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('149', '285', '&lt;p&gt;A 52 yr old male attends for his routine blood check. He has a blood pressure of 150/88. He also states he is a smoker. In discussions surrounding smoking which one of the following best describes “pack years”?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"The total number of years that an individual has been smoked for.\",\"One pack year equates to the smoking of twenty cigarettes a day for one year\",\"The number of packs that a person smokes per day\",\"A calculation used to quantify exposure to tobacco smoke in a standardised manner\",\"The number of years that a person has smoked for before developing symptoms of a smoking related disorder\"]', '[\"2\"]', '5'), ('150', '287', '&lt;p&gt;If someone says that mood is low you should...&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"Just reassure them that it\'s normal for teenagers\",\"Make an instant referral to CAMHS\",\"Screen for self-harm and suicidality\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('151', '287', '&lt;p&gt;What is the most common mental health problem in children and adolescents&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"Depression\",\"Anxiety\",\"ADHD\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('152', '297', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these statements is correct? (1 correct answer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"Proper disposal of medical waste does not help control infections.\",\"Proper disposal of medical waste does not help the spreading of infections.\",\"Proper disposal of medical waste minimises the spread of infections.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '1'), ('153', '297', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these statements is correct? (1 correct answer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"Disinfection is not one of the levels of decontamination.\",\"Cleaning is not one of the levels of decontamination.\",\"Sterilisation is one of the levels of decontamination.\"]', '[\"3\"]', '2'), ('154', '297', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these statements is correct? (1 correct answer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '3', '[\"Good infection prevention practices protect everyone.\",\"Good infection prevention practices protect only employees.\",\"Good infection prevention practices protect only clients.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '3'), ('155', '303', '&lt;p&gt;hronic obstructive pulmonary disease, or COPD, includes the diagnosis of which lung diseases?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Emphysema\",\"Chronic Bronchitis\",\"Neither\",\"Both\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('156', '303', '&lt;p&gt;Complete the following. COPD is:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"A disease that only occurs in smokers\",\"A common condition in young people\",\"Rare and incurable\",\"A condition whose symptoms can be managed with medication and stopping smoking\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('157', '303', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following symptoms do COPD sufferers often experience?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Shortness of breath\",\"Constant fatigue\",\"A chronic cough that produce phlegm\",\"All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('158', '303', '&lt;p&gt;COPD makes it harder to breathe because&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"The walls of the airways in the lungs become thick and inflamed\",\"Lungs lose their elasticity\",\"Excess mucus in the airways\",\"All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('159', '303', '&lt;p&gt;Why is COPD underdiagnosed?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"The symptoms are often mild and may go unnoticed.\",\"The disease is so rare that doctors don\'t recognize the symptoms.\",\"There are no reliable tests to diagnose COPD.\",\"The rapid progression of the disease means patients often die before it can be diagnosed.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('168', '326', '&lt;p&gt;A 58-year-old man with a BMI of 32 comes to the surgery. He states he gets very short of breath after climbing a flight of stairs. His SOB is associated with a cough and productive green sputum. He has had symptoms like these for at least four months out of the year over the past decade, but they have been consistently present for the past 6 months and seem to be worsening in severity. The patient admits to smoking about a pack of cigarettes a week for the past 20 years. He has never received flu vaccine. He is worried that this could be related to his family history of cardiac issues. He is afebrile, there is no sign of oedema and heart sounds appear to be normal. Which of the following findings is most likely to be observed on physical examination?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"COPD\",\"Asthma\",\"Obstructive Sleep Apnoea\",\"Heart Failure\",\"Emphysema\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('170', '326', '&lt;p&gt;A 30-year-old man comes to the clinic because of fatigue and sleepiness throughout the day. His past medical, family, and social histories are non-contributory. His wife says he snores very loudly while sleeping and she has recently noticed that he will stop breathing.momentarily, multiple times throughout the night. spo2: 90%. He has a BMI of 33kg/m2, having gained 5.4-kg (12-lb) over the past year without any significant lifestyle or dietary changes. You advise the patient to lose weight and see a relevant specialist. Which is the most likely cause of this patient’s condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Anaemia\",\"Obstructive Sleep Apnoea\",\"Orthopnea\",\"Diabetes Mellitus\",\"Heart Failure\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('171', '326', '&lt;p&gt;A 23-year-old college student comes to the surgery with a 2 day history of a non-productive cough, feeling feverish and “feeling sick” for 2 days. She says she has a final exam tomorrow and wants some medicine so she feels better during the test. Her temperature is 37.2°C, P87/min, RR18/min, and BP 117/78 mm Hg. Examination shows clear lung sounds bilaterally in all fields. There is no cervical lymphadenopathy. She has some pharyngeal erythema with neither exudates nor vesicles. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in the management of this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Refer to emergency department for intravenous antibiotics\",\"Refer for chest x-ray\",\"Discharge with oral antibiotics\",\"Reassure and discharge\",\"Give oral steroids\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('172', '326', '&lt;p&gt;A 5-year-old girl is brought to the emergency department by her parents because of a sore throat and difficulty swallowing that began 3 days ago. Her temperature is 39.2 °C , pulse is 92/minute, respiration rate 22/minute, and blood pressure is 100/73 mm Hg. Her O2 saturation of 98% on room air. Physical examination shows an erythematous oropharynx, bilateral tonisillar exudates, and cervical lymphadenopathy. During the examination, the patient resists moving her head and begins drooling. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Meningitis\",\"Croup\",\"Epiglottitis\",\"Peritonsillar abscess\",\"Retropharyngeal abscess\"]', '[\"5\"]', '0'), ('173', '326', '&lt;p&gt;46-year-old man comes to the surgery with 3 day history of shortness of breath and increasing difficulty in breathing. He has a productive cough with green and yellow phlegm, with dyspnea that worsens with minimal exertion. He has experienced no fever, chills or chest pain. He is otherwise generally well except from a morning cough that brings up white sputum which he has been for many years. He has a 40 pack year history of smoking. No immunization history. SPO2 88% on room air and no cyanosis. Prolonged expiratory phase and bilateral expiry wheeze on auscultation. What is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Acute exacerbation of COPD\",\"Bronchial pneumonia\",\"Bronchiectasis\",\"Congestive cardiac failure\",\"Viral pneumonia\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('174', '329', '&lt;p&gt;A 65-year-old woman comes to the office because of problems with her hearing and ‘ear fullness.’ She reports that she has noticed a low pitch noise that others don’t hear that sounds like being by rthe ocean, and a decrease in hearing in her left ear. She has also been having intermittent episodes of dizziness when she feels like the room is spinning. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis for this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Labyrinthitis\",\"Meniere\\u2019s Disease\",\"BPPV\",\"Migraine with aura\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('175', '329', '&lt;p&gt;A 25yr old male comes to the out of hours clinic with an inability to open his mouth. He has pain and swelling in his neck which has worsened over the past day. He has bilateral swelling of the floor of the mouth involving his submandibular and sublingual glands. His molars on the right side are decayed and there is an abscess around the back molars. The skin of his upper neck is red but intact. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Ludwig\\u2019s Angina\",\"Kawasaki Disease\",\"Sialolithiasis\",