s. The skin of his upper neck is red but intact. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Periodontitis\",\"Sialolithiasis\",\"Kawasaki Disease\",\"Ludwig\\u2019s Angina\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('191', '345', '&lt;p&gt;A 53-year-old woman comes to the office because she thinks her hearing has worsened in her left ear. She has not noticed any discharge or felt any dizziness. Her temperature is 37.3 °C P: 72 RR:12 and BP : 132/78. She has conductive hearing loss in left ear. Physical examination shows no erythema or tenderness of the pinna or auricle. The ear examination shows a retracted tympanic membrane and squamous debris. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Mastoiditis\",\"Impacted wax\",\"Chronic Otitis Media\",\"Cholesteatoma\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('192', '345', '&lt;p&gt;22 Year old female presents with a history of vertigo, nausea and tinnitus for 2 days. Recent upper respiratory tract infection that was treated with anti virals. She has mild hearing loss and a positive Dix-Hallpike manoeuver. Based on the patient’s history and symptoms, which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"BPPV\",\"Labyrinthitis\",\"Vestibular Neuritis\",\"Meniere\\u2019s disease\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('193', '345', '&lt;p&gt;A previously healthy 5-year-old boy comes to the office because of fever for the past two days. His mother reports onset of vomiting and dysphagia earlier this morning but denies any diarrhea, rhinorrhea or upper respiratory symptoms. She notes that he just started kindergarten, and there have been a few other children out sick. His temperature is 38.8°C (101.9°F). His posterior oropharynx is erythematous with an inflamed uvula and enlarged symmetric masses. He also has enlarged, tender anterior cervical lymphadenopathy. He is quite resistant, constantly moving his head to avoid the examination. Which of the following is the most appropriate treatment?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Immediate surgical drainage by ENT\",\"Oral penicillin\",\"Rest and paracetamol\",\"Tonsillectomy\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('194', '348', '&lt;p&gt;To what drug does paroxysmal hemicrania respond well?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Amitriptyline\",\"Topiramate\",\"Verapamil\",\"Indomethacin\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('195', '348', '&lt;p&gt;35-year-old female presents to the surgery complaining of right-sided facial pain. She is complaining of/o stabbing electric shocks exacerbated by eating, brushing her teeth and a brisk breeze across her face. The pain lasts a few seconds and rarely up to a couple of minutes. Physical examination shows normal facial sensation, normal bulk in the masseters bilaterally, and intact extra-ocular muscles. Which is the most appropriate treatment in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Calcium Gluconate\",\"Carbamazepine\",\"Valproic acid\",\"Clonazepam\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('196', '348', '&lt;p&gt;48yr old females comes to the surgery at 14h00 complaining of headache since 3am that day. She is complaining that the pain is unilateral and throbbing in nature. The patient says she was watching her sons school rehearsal not long before the onset of the headache. She says the rehearsal used strobe lighting for visual effects. She also mentions hallucinating light beams ‘dancing in front of her’ after the show. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Migraine\",\"SAH\",\"Cluster Headache\",\"Epilepsy\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('197', '348', '&lt;p&gt;28yr old female presents with a severe headache that started 4hrs ago. Describes the headache as pulsating and localised to right eye. No relief with paracetamol and ibuprofen. Which of the following drugs would you consider helping with her acute symptoms?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Metoclopramide\",\"Naproxen\",\"Ondansetron\",\"Sumatriptan\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('198', '348', '&lt;p&gt;40-year-old male attends the out of hours centre complaining of a severe headache that woke him from his sleep about 4 hrs ago. Complaining of a stabbing and burning pain located behind his right eye. He also has nasal congestion on that side He had something similar around the same month 5yrs ago. He gets these every year at the same time. PMH nil except he smokes for past 30 years about one pack a day. Physical examination reveals normal intraocular pressures bilaterally, normal visual acuity, and no fluorescein dye uptake on either cornea. His right eyelid is drooping with slight pupil constriction. Which of the following is the most appropriate preventative measure for this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Verapamil\",\"Propranolol\",\"Sumatriptan\",\"Paracetamol\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('199', '353', '&lt;p&gt;A 36yr old male comes to the surgery complaining of of pain in both legs that has been progressively worsening for 2 years. He states that the pain is especially debilitating when he walks, but is still present at rest and when he awakes in the morning. What could he possibly have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Nerve root compression\",\"Spinal stenosis\",\"Atherosclerotic vessels\",\"Schwann cell tumour\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('200', '353', '&lt;p&gt;A 70-year-old man comes to the internal medicine outpatient clinic for regular follow-up. 10-years ago, he underwent a surgery for stomach cancer. He reports that he has been feeling fatigued for the past 3 months. He also notes a tingling sensation in his toes and fingers. Physical examination shows bilateral brisk knee reflexes and loss of proprioception. bilaterally. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Diabetes mellitus\",\"Vitamin B12 deficiency\",\"Colon cancer\",\"Folate deficiency\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('201', '353', '&lt;p&gt;A 22-year-old female attends the surgery complaining of urinary incontinence. She tells you that she had ‘spine problems’ as a child, including scoliosis. She has a history of recurrent lower back pain. She was at her physiotherapist today when she suddenly developed weakness and incontinence.. She says the back pain radiates to her legs and perineum and she feels a bit numb in her genitalia. Her friend helped her to get to the surgery which was next to physiotherapy. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Spinal stenosis\",\"Cauda equina\",\"Cerebrovascular accident\",\"Impaired ability of the detrusor muscle to contract\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('202', '353', '&lt;p&gt;A 36yr old male comes to the surgery complaining of pain in both legs that has been progressively worsening for 2 years. He states that the pain is especially debilitating when he walks, but is still present at rest and when he awakes in the morning. No numbness or paraesthesia. What could he possibly have? (Select all that apply)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Vascular claudication\",\"Spinal stenosis\",\"Neurogenic claudication\",\"Sciatica\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('203', '353', '&lt;p&gt;A 42-year-old woman comes to the clinic because of fatigue, IRRITABILITY AND NUMBNES AND TINGLING in her legs and hands. She has increasing difficulty with walking, especially at night. Laboratory studies show megaloblastic and macrocytic and anaemia with hypersegmented neutrophils and anti-parietal cell antibodies. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Folic acid deficiency type\",\"Diabetes Mellitus\",\"Stroke\",\"Pernicious anaemia\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('204', '357', '&lt;p&gt;25-year-old man comes to the surgery because of severe leg cramps. He says that he has \\”dark urine\\” and that earlier in the morning he had trouble lifting a glass object object. Physical examination shows tenderness in his hamstrings and quadriceps when palpated. Urine dipstick is positive for blood. Which of the following is most likely a potential complication of this patient’s condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Acute Myocardial Infarction\",\"Acute kidney injury\",\"Haemothorax\",\"Acute respiratory distress syndrome\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('205', '357', '&lt;p&gt;A 48-year-old woman comes to the emergency department because of ‘burning, bloody urine’. She has been urinating more frequently for the past 2 days, but she denies polydipsia, vaginal discharge, back pain, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, or fevers. Physical examination shows that she is afebrile and her other vital signs are stable. Her abdomen is soft, non-tender and there is no flank tenderness. Urine dipstick is positive for leukocyte esterase and nitrites. Which of the following is the most appropriate initial treatment option?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Doxycycline\",\"amoxycillin\",\"Nitrofurantoin\",\"Trimethoprim\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('206', '357', '&lt;p&gt;A 27-year-old man comes to the surgery because of severe flank pain for an hour. The pain woke him from his sleep, He rates the pain as a 10 on a 10-point scale. Temperature is 36.7°. He appears to be constantly moving and unable to get comfortable. No medical problems. Had kidney stones about a year ago but since then he has been well. What is the likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Appendicitis\",\"Ruptured bladder\",\"Small bowel obstruction\",\"Hydronephrosis\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('207', '357', '&lt;p&gt;A 50-year-old woman comes to the surgery because of severe, colicky left-sided abdominal pain. Urinalysis shows trace of blood. Her T: 37.2° , P:70. RR18 and BP: 160/90 mm Hg. Her BMI is 23. Her medical history is significant for celiac disease that was diagnosed 20 years ago. She avoids gluten and takes vitamins to “stay healthy”. Which of the following is most likely present in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Osteomalacia\",\"Vitamin D excess\",\"Vitamin D deficiency\",\"Vitamin C deficiency\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('208', '357', '&lt;p&gt;A 25-year-old previously healthy woman comes to the surgery because of 2 days of mild nausea and vomiting. She denies recent sick contacts or eating anything out of the ordinary. She has maintained good oral intake of food and fluids over the past two days, but has noticed increasing malaise and a dull pain on her right side. She complains of mild dysuria and urinary frequency for the past 2 days. Medical history is negative for kidney stones T:38.3P:100 RR:18 BP: 11/70 Physical examination shows no definite CVA tenderness. Urine dipstick positive for leucocytes. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis? Select all that apply&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"UTI\",\"Acute cystitis\",\"Kidney stones\",\"Appendicitis\"]', '[\"1\",\"2\"]', '0'), ('209', '364', '&lt;p&gt;A 10-year old girl is brought to her pediatrician’s office by her parents because of a new onset of skin lesions for the past 3 days. Her father says that the patient had an initial lesion of a small pustule which quickly progressed into an extensive rash. Physical examination shows the following: Which of the following is the most likely causative organism?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Human herpes virus 6\",\"Varicella-zoster virus\",\"Staphylococcus aureus\",\"Streptococcus agalactia\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('210', '364', '&lt;p&gt;A 19-year-old man comes to the clinic because of a rash that started as a single lesion a few days ago. It has since spread throughout his chest and back. The patient had an upper respiratory infection nine days ago. Physical examination shows salmon pink patches, as seen below. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Pityriasis Rosea\",\"Syphillis\",\"Porphyria\",\"Tinea Corporis\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('211', '364', '&lt;p&gt;A 36-year-old man who recently emigrated from Chile comes to the physician for a wellness checkup. He states that he had worked as a farmer for many years. His jobs included spraying plants with pesticide, harvesting crops, and plowing the fields. The pesticide he worked with contains arsenic. Which of the following skin conditions is he most at risk for developing?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Acral lentiginous melanoma\",\"Dishydrotic eczema\",\"Basal cell carcinoma\",\"Squamous cell carcinoma\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('212', '364', '&lt;p&gt;A 73-year-old male comes to the office with a itchy skin rash. The lesions are round, oval, and erythematous on both legs. There is noticeable xerosis of the affected skin. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Tinea corporis\",\"Seborrheic keratosis\",\"Nummular eczema\",\"Tinea versicolor\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('213', '364', '&lt;p&gt;A 22-year-old woman comes to the clinic because of blisters on her hands. She recently got a summer job designing costumes for a local theatre production group. She says that the lesions first appeared on the lateral edges of her fingers and then spread to her palms. The lesions are very itchy and somewhat tender. Physical examination shows tense vesicles on her fingers and the palms of her hands without any associated erythema. Which of the following is true about this condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"The lesions are associated with sweat gland dysfunction\",\"Triggered by exposure to nickel\",\"Associated with coeliac disease\",\"It is psoriasis\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('214', '372', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is NOT a common food allergen&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '2', '[\"Peanuts\",\"Mustard\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('215', '372', '&lt;p&gt;Where is the best place to inject with an autoinjector pen?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"The thigh\",\"The arm\",\"The stomach\",\"The neck\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('216', '372', '&lt;p&gt;If you are at risk for anaphylaxis, the best way to manage your condition is:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Avoid allergens that trigger symptoms\",\"Carry autoinjectable epinephrine\",\"Know how to use epinephrine\",\"All of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('217', '377', '&lt;p&gt;A 20-year-old female presents with a 5 day history of vaginal discharge. Sexually active but not using contraception. Has had same partner for past year. Pelvic examination shows normal external genitalia. There is a moderate amount of malodorous, thin, gray discharge coating the vaginal walls. The vulva and cervix appear normal. There is no cervical motion tenderness on bimanual examination. The pH of the vaginal fluid is 5.0. Swabs show that patient has a bacterial infection. Symptoms consistent with bacterial vaginosis. A urine pregnancy test is negative. Which of the following is the most appropriate pharmacologic treatment?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Metronidazole\",\"Ceftriaxone\",\"Miconazole\",\"Azithromycin\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('218', '377', '&lt;p&gt;A 23-year-old woman comes to the clinic because of a change in vaginal discharge. Over the past week she has noticed a foul smelling discharge, particularly after intercourse. She denies any pain, itching or irregular bleeding. She has an intrauterine contraceptive device that was inserted 2 years ago. Vital signs are normal. Physical examination shows a foul-smelling, thin, whitish-gray vaginal discharge. There is no adnexal or cervical motion tenderness on bimanual examination.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Gonococcal urethritis\",\"Trichomonas vaginitis\",\"Bacterial vaginosis\",\"Candidiasis\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('219', '377', '&lt;p&gt;A 35-year-old woman comes to the office because of a 5-day history of increasing vaginal discharge accompanied by vaginal pruritus and burning. She reports discomfort during sexual intercourse. Genitourinary examination shows vulvar erythema with a thick white discharge. Swabs show vulovaginitis. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Amoxicillin\",\"Doxycycline\",\"Testing of sexual partners\",\"Fluconazole\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('220', '377', '&lt;p&gt;A 25-year-old woman comes to the office for an examination. She is a student and exercises regularly. She is sexually active with a partner and uses oral contraceptive pills. Medical history is noncontributory. Family history includes a grandmother with coronary artery disease. Her temperature is 36.8°C (98°F), pulse is 87/min, respirations are 18/min, and blood pressure is 152/91 mm Hg. Physical examination shows no abnormalities. Over the next 3 months, her blood pressure is repeatedly elevated at clinic visits. Which of the following is the most appropriate first step in management?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Alprazolam\",\"Cessation of oral contraceptive pills\",\"Hydrochlorothiazide\",\"Lisinopril\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('221', '377', '&lt;p&gt;A 21 yr old female presents to the surgery complaining of pain during intercourse. She gives a history of unprotected sex with multiple partners. No recent pregnancy. Physical exam nad, except for moderate cervical motion tenderness while performing pelvic exam. What condition could she possibly have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Candidiasis\",\"Chlamydia\",\"Gonorrheoa\",\"Bacterial Vaginosis\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('222', '383', '&lt;p&gt;Tazocin is a penicillin and must not be given to patients who have had anaphylaxis when given flucloxacillin.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"True\",\"False\",\"Can be given to some patients\",\"Can be used with caution in some patients with penicillin allergy.\"]', '[\"1\"]', '1'), ('223', '383', '&lt;p&gt;Which antibiotic(s) can be used in a patient who has had an anaphylactic reaction to penicillin?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Gentamicin\",\"Ciprofloxacin\",\"Clarithromycin\",\"a,b and c\",\"None of the above\"]', '[\"4\"]', '2'), ('224', '384', '&lt;p&gt;A 5-year old boy comes to the office because of irritated red eyes and decreased vision for the past two days. According to his mother, several children in his class have had similar symptoms. Physical examination shows 20/30 visual acuity in both eyes and conjunctival injection and watery discharge bilaterally. He also has mildly enlarged, tender lymph nodes just anterior to his ears. Which of the following organisms is the most likely cause of his condition?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Pseudomonas Aeroginosa\",\"Staphylococcus aureus\",\"Mumps virus\",\"Adenovirus\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('225', '383', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following are NOT effective in preventing the emergence or spread of antibiotic resistant pathogens ?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '5', '[\"Adherence to hand hygiene\",\"Contact isolation during hospitalisation for patients colonised with MRSA\",\"Avoiding the use of antibiotics for viral infections\",\"Treating infections for a longer duration\",\"Treating infections for shorter duration\"]', '[\"4\"]', '3'), ('226', '384', '&lt;p&gt;A 60-year-old man comes to the surgery&amp;nbsp; because of a severe headache for 30 minutes. He describes a left-sided headache and eye pain. He has felt nauseous and vomited twice. The patient has a long history of migraines but denies usually getting eye pain with them. His temperature is 36.5°C; P: 84 RR12/min, and BP:134/86. His neuro exam is normal. Eye examination shows his left eye is mid-dilated and nonreactive. His left cornea is also cloudy. His best corrected&amp;nbsp; VA is 24/6&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;in the left eye and 6/6 in the right eye. Which condition does he likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Subarachnoid haemorrhage\",\"Eye migraine\",\"Acute angle closure glaucoma\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('227', '384', '&lt;p&gt;A 68yr old afro-carribean female presents with increasingly poor peripheral vision. No pain, swelling or discomfort around the eye. No rashes. No recent trauma. Pt has a history of diabetes and hypothyroidism. She takes metformin and levothyroxine. On examination there is some visual field deficits peripherally. Blood pressure : 150/88. P; 72. No new joint pain or fatigue. Which condition does this patient likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple sclerosis\",\"Open angle glaucoma\",\"Closed angle glaucoma\",\"Cataracts\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('228', '384', '&lt;p&gt;A 30yr old male of Turkish origin presents with poor vision for a week. He saw the optometrist and was presecribed some glasses as his vision is 18/6 both eyes. He has only just started using glasses and didn’t have previous vision problems. He states that he has also experienced painful ulcers in his mouth during the same period. Also gives a history of painful joints and mouth ulcers recently. No other significant medical history. Fundus examination shows white, superficial infiltrates. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Vitamin B12 deficiency\",\"Reiters disease\",\"Behcets Disease\",\"Multiple Sclerosis\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('229', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('230', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('231', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('232', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('233', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('234', '384', '&lt;p&gt;38yr old female presents with a history with not sleeping well for past 3 months. She feels increasingly tired. Finds it difficult to fall asleep at night. On examination, she has a droopy rt eye, anhidrosis and miosis on the rt side. No recent viral infection and no other medical history. BP: 120/72 P: 70 RR:16.T: 36.2. What condition does she likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Multiple Sclerosis\",\"Horners Syndrome\",\"Bells Palsy\",\"Stroke\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('235', '388', '&lt;p&gt;56yr old male with a history of chronic fatigue attends the surgery. He states he has difficulty sleeping and finds it hard to concentrate. you notice he has called 111 a few times and come to the surgery with similar symptoms 3 times in the past month. Which condition does he likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Schizophrenia\",\"Obsessive Compulsive Disorder\",\"Generalised anxiety Disorder\",\"Psychosis\"]', '[\"3\"]', '0'), ('236', '388', '&lt;p&gt;A 85-year-old male attends a surgery appointment accompanied by his wife. She complains that his memory has been gradually getting worse and that he has difficulty buttoning his shirt. On interviewing him, you find that he has trouble finding words. Which condition does he likely have?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Parkinsons\",\"Alzheimers\",\"Delirium\",\"Schizophrenia\"]', '[\"2\"]', '0'), ('237', '388', '&lt;p&gt;18yr old patient presents with her mother who is concerned as daughter regularly abuses alcohol and has multiple sexual partners. Physical examination shows numerous cuts on her forearm. Which of the following is most likely present in this patient?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Borderline personality disorders\",\"Histrionic personality disorder\",\"Narcissistic personality disorder\",\"Obsessive compulsive personality disorder\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('238', '396', '&lt;p&gt;Tazocin is a penicillin and must not be given to patients who have had anaphylaxis when given flucloxacillin.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"True\",\"False\",\"Can be given to some patients\",\"Can be given to patients who are not immunocompromised\"]', '[\"1\"]', '0'), ('239', '396', '&lt;p&gt;Which antibiotic(s) can be used in a patient who has had an anaphylactic reaction to penicillin?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Gentamicin\",\"Ciprofloxacin\",\"Clarithromycin\",\"a,b and c\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('240', '396', '&lt;p&gt;Which of the following are NOT effective in preventing the emergence or spread of antibiotic resistant pathogens ?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Adherence to hand hygiene\",\"Contact isolation during hospitalisation for patients colonised with MRSA\",\"Avoiding the use of antibiotics for viral infections\",\"Treating infections for a longer duration\"]', '[\"4\"]', '0'), ('241', '396', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these antibiotics have useful clinical activity against pseudomonas? Select all that apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Ciprofloxacin\",\"Co-amoxiclav\",\"Ceftazidime\",\"Cefotaxime\"]', '[\"1\",\"3\"]', '0'), ('242', '396', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these would be suitable to treat Gram positive cocci isolated from a blood culture? Select all that apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Flucloxacillin\",\"Vancomycin\",\"Ciprofloxacin\",\"Trimethoprim\"]', '[\"1\",\"2\"]', '0'), ('243', '383', '&lt;p&gt;Which of these antibiotics have useful clinical activity against pseudomonas? Select all that apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'multiple_choice', '4', '[\"Ciprofloxacin\",\"Ceftazidime\",\"Cefotaxime\",\"Co-amoxiclav\"]', '[\"2\"]', '4'), ('244', '383', '&lt;p&gt;Wh