est minor illness and injuries.</p><p>My hobbies are supporting my lifelong team Brentford FC where I am a season ticket holder.<br></p>', '2', NULL, '1697377563', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', 'ddb261575efcf83e3a6c5433215a109a', ''), ('15', 'Kenny', 'Gibson', NULL, 'Kenny@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '64e8cd5e8cc547dc274849acb5d436823ebb4fcd', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<p><b>National Head of Safeguarding for the NHS </b></p><p>Kenny Gibson is the National Head of Safeguarding for the NHS, overseeing several portfolios including tackling abuse, exploitation, radicalisation and violence. He leads nationally on Contextual Safeguarding; Trauma Informed Care; Prevent in the NHS and Child Protection Information System. Having begun his NHS career as a laundry assistant in 1980 at a mental health unit, Kenny was encouraged to become a nursing assistant and then trained as a nurse and then a midwife. Kenny has held various operational, management and strategic posts in both community and public health but always with nursing at the heart of these roles. Prior to becoming the Head of Safeguarding for NHS England, Kenny was the Head of Public Health Commissioning for London. Kenny is passionate about connecting with and listening to patients, carers and health practitioners in order to improve services and experiences within the NHS, as well as to empower people about their own well-being. You can follow Kenny on Twitter at: @KennyGibsonNHS or @NHSSafeguarding Kenny Gibson is the National Head of Safeguarding for the NHS, overseeing several portfolios including tackling abuse, exploitation, radicalisation and violence. He leads nationally on Contextual Safeguarding; Trauma Informed Care; Prevent in the NHS and Child Protection Information System. Having begun his NHS career as a laundry assistant in 1980 at a mental health unit, Kenny was encouraged to become a nursing assistant and then trained as a nurse and then a midwife. Kenny has held various operational, management and strategic posts in both community and public health but always with nursing at the heart of these roles. Prior to becoming the Head of Safeguarding for NHS England, Kenny was the Head of Public Health Commissioning for London. Kenny is passionate about connecting with and listening to patients, carers and health practitioners in order to improve services and experiences within the NHS, as well as to empower people about their own well-being. You can follow Kenny on Twitter at: @KennyGibsonNHS or @NHSSafeguarding<br></p>', '2', NULL, '1697377925', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '0d0ebb4718231e6b85c95e1e1413b18a', ''), ('17', 'Dr Hayley', ' Jenkins', NULL, 'hayley@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '20eabe5d64b0e216796e834f52d61fd0b70332fc', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<h3 xss=removed>Family planning and women’s health</h3><p xss=removed>Dr Hayley Jenkins has an extensive history in Family planning and women’s health. She spent her GP reg year was with a doctor who specialised in family planning (FP) and women’s health too. During that time she achieved her DFSRH and LOC for coils and implants and has since become a FP trainer. As a partner in a larger training practice, she developed a weekly FP clinic and trained other doctors. Dr Jenkins worked with the local sexual health clinic in addition to her GP role and has since had roles as a FP trainer.</p><p xss=removed>And in her own words:</p><p xss=removed>“Initially this was just 2.5hrs a fortnight but over time these hours increased, and I was able to reduce my core GP hours to accommodate. The more I’ve trained and worked in family planning the more specialist skills I’ve mastered mainly through practice and experience rather than exams and qualifications. I became known in Milton Keynes as an expert in my field and was then approached to lecture and teach local GPs and nurses. I secured a bid with my practice to run a community gynae clinic working alongside a local consultant – pushing my skills to another level. Looking back at my career, it’s made up of three key components, GP, women’s health and teaching/training. I value them all equally and like the diversity this brings to my working life.</p><p xss=removed>I now work as a salaried GP one day a week where I mainly focus on menopause and women’s health. I am also the contraception lead for Milton Keynes and Bedford Sexual health services. I enjoy all these roles very much and hope to continue them for a long time to come.</p>', '2', NULL, '1698244244', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', 'f13250369edfb692205779cbdd05cbab', ''), ('18', 'Dr Parmy', 'Deol', NULL, 'parmy@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<p><b>A&E consultant at Chelsea and Westminster Hospital and dual trained GP. </b></p><p>Dr Deol leads the urgent care centre at Chelsea and teaches extensively on innovative methods of practice. Dr Deol provides training on blood results interpretation and teaches on the minor illness modules. His other teachings include training on point of care ultrasound to support diagnosis in primary care.<br></p>', '2', NULL, '1698244340', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '701ae1a9042a438254c5395c55a23856', ''), ('19', 'Dr Ahmed', 'Kazmi', NULL, 'ahmed@belmatt.co,uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '', '2', NULL, '1698244422', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', 'a8679dfe28d295dfa867157207e57a4b', ''), ('20', 'Neil ', 'Humber ', NULL, 'neil@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '', '2', NULL, '1698244500', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '93cb907e9784a6c0c115e507d8035af7', ''), ('21', 'Dr Jose ', 'Crespo', NULL, 'Jose@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<p><b>General Practitioner</b><br></p>', '2', NULL, '1698244563', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '548881ec0eb1a315213a66cec6e48867', ''), ('22', 'Dr Leah', 'Brennan', NULL, 'Leah@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<h3 xss=removed>Chartered Clinical Psychologist</h3><p xss=removed>Leah is a Chartered Clinical Psychologist who is a full member and Associate fellow of the British Psychological Society. She is registered with the Health Professionals Council and has over 20 years’ experience working in both the UK and Australia providing psychological assessments and treatment to children, young people and their families.</p><p xss=removed>Leah has trained educators on the management of anxiety in schools and has experience across a range of clinical settings including anxiety disorders, parenting, childhood sexual abuse and looked after children. Working in independent practice in Hertfordshire at Mindscape Psychology, Leah works together with children and their families using modern, evidence-based therapy. In addition, she is an established senior NHS Clinical Psychologist within the Paediatric Team at The Hillingdon Hospitals in West London supporting children with medical conditions</p>', '2', NULL, '1698244631', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', 'ad492837611ffae1dbfbec446e3ea8dc', ''), ('23', 'Dorthe', ' Swaby', NULL, 'Dorthe@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<h3 xss=removed>MSc, BSc (Hons), RGN, PGCert HE-Lecturer-Practice Educator (NMC Registered), PGCert Leadership-Management, Non-Medical Prescriber</h3><p xss=removed>An experienced Advanced Nurse Practitioner with over thirty years of experience spanning Emergency and Urgent Care nursing. Dorthe worked as a Nurse Consultant for twelve years in South London and as Deputy Head of Nursing, for King’s College Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. She worked as Lecturer Practitioner for Middlesex University and has continued her passion for teaching and training by lecturing and teaching freelance. Dorthe (in association with a Director of Nursing) established a university accredited Urgent Care Training Programme for Emergency successfully delivered Emergency Practitioner’s competent to work with adults and children with  Minor Injuries and Illnesses within an Urgent Care setting. Dorthe is also widely published having co-written Limb X-ray Interpretation (2006) as well as numerous Nursing journal publications</p><p xss=removed>Dorthe has particular experience and interests in Minor Injuries- wound management and limb X-ray Interpretation</p>', '2', NULL, '1698244702', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '0c8e94c902d5973206ca6872b09bbc7b', ''), ('24', 'Gill', 'Dunn', NULL, 'gill@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<h3 xss=removed>Diabetes Nurse Specialist</h3><p xss=removed>Gill Dunn began specialising in diabetes in 1990, working as a practice nurse for 13 years and then ten years as a specialist diabetes nurse working on an insulin education programme.</p><p xss=removed>In 2013 she joined Buckinghamshire CCG and her current role involves educational and clinical support for all healthcare professionals in primary care. Her work also involves developing the local diabetes pathway and new guidelines.<br>The role allows her to work in collaboration with teams from all areas of healthcare, including Medicines Management, CCG, Primary, Secondary, Community Care, Mental Health teams and Public Health.<br>Recent projects include the National Diabetes Audit for Pregnancy project, developing Pre and Post-operative guidelines and Diabetes in Remission policy.</p><p xss=removed>She is committed to improving diabetes care for all people with diabetes and especially the elderly and frail, where she successfully initiated a programme of education for care and nursing home staff for which she has won a poster award, presented at a national conference and wrote a journal for the Diabetes UK ‘Balance’ magazine. This work was also used in her successful application to become a Queen’s Nurse in 2018.</p>', '2', NULL, '1698244773', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"production_secret_key\":\"\"},\"stripe\":{\"public_key\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"public_live_key\":\"\",\"secret_live_key\":\"\"},\"razorpay\":{\"key_id\":\"\",\"secret_key\":\"\",\"theme_color\":\"\"}}', NULL, '1', '1', '6005eea89e5f107c7eaaa4d9682699c9', ''), ('25', 'Lala ', 'Dizon', NULL, 'lal@belmatt.co.uk', '', '', '8cb2237d0679ca88db6464eac60da96345513964', '', '{\"facebook\":\"\",\"twitter\":\"\",\"linkedin\":\"\"}', '<p>Lala is an advanced practitioner with a long history as a resuscitation officer at St. Georges University and now the Royal Marsden Hospital.<br></p>', '2', NULL, '1698244903', NULL, '[]', NULL, '{\"paypal\":{\"sandbox_client_id\":\"\",\"sandbox_secret_key\":\"\",\"production_client_id\":\"\",\"